title: Mexico down USA 3-2 to book Confederations Cup spot
text:
Mexico down USA 3-2 to book Confederations Cup spot Published: 11 October 2015 12:36 PM 
Mexico celebrates the goal scored by defender Paul Aguilar (22) against USA in extra time of the CONCACAF Cup at Rose Bowl. – Reuters pic, October 11, 2015. Mexico stunned the United States 3-2 to qualify for the 2017 Confederations Cup yesterday as a spectacular extra-time winner from Paul Aguilar settled a five-goal thriller at the Pasadena Rose Bowl. 
Mexico defender Aguilar lashed in a dramatic volley in the 118th minute to spark euphoric scenes at the iconic venue in front of 93,723 fans. – AFP, October 11,
